PlayerPro Legacy is not recognized as a music player from any other apps. Can I suggest an option to enable thumbprint of abum art next to song when in artists & songs tab (like folders tab). Great app but 5 stars when glitch fixed.

If you're looking for a music player, Version 2 (Legacy) is the one I recommend, not Version 3. PlayerPro 2 is a great and extremely capable player, especially when used in a car or dock. Version 3 is less convenient and costs more. Version 2 works as it always has -- although it does (incorrectly) complain that the DSP Pack is not compatible. I'm sorry I had to pay for version 2 again, but that the developers are continuing to make it available seems like a bonus, not a ripoff, to me.

(S5) And also, the font color for the techno skins are dark for the title of the songs and the techno red is the only one that has the red font in the title names. The dark font makes it almost impossible to see in the daytime, especially when you're driving and trying to find the next song you want to play. So I only use the techno red theme.
